The recorder's `Layer.effect` receives the `MetricsRecorder` tag so the returned layer produces exactly that service, while yielding `MetricsBackend` makes the dependency explicit in the R channel before `Layer.merge` eliminates it.

Layers build services from their dependencies. `Layer.succeed` injects a ready-made value, `Layer.effect` constructs one inside an `Effect` (can `yield*` other services), and `Layer.merge` / `Layer.mergeAll` combine independent layers. `Effect.provide` finally feeds a program the composed `Layer`, erasing service tags from the R channel.

